	   <tr><td colspan=2>The faster weapon in GENERAL should be in your primary hand because of the damage bonus.&nbsp;&nbsp;The damage bonus applies to primary hand only, on each swing of your weapon, so (all else being equal), a faster attack is better.<br><br>HOWEVER, if you have two weapons of varying stats, the damage done by the better weapon may be enough to overcome the benefit of having the bonus applied more often on the weapon with higher speed.  I believe this would be the case in the example you site, although I haven't run the numbers myself.  Note that at level 40, when you get another increase to your damage bonus, the Fighting Baton may become the better primary hand weapon.<br><br>Also, make sure you're using the right equations for calculating total damage output.  There are a lot of bad 'figurators' out there.  I think the info at www.monkly-business.com is, on the whole, the most reliable.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
