	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just after I finished my first response, I found this link.<br><br><a href="http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html" target=_new>http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html</a><br><br>It basically answers my question.&nbsp;&nbsp;With the info there, I've determined that at lvl 39 (and at 40 for that matter) the FB in primary and the CoT in secondary is SLIGHTLY better than the other way around.  The table at that link indicate that I will do 10.39 dam/sec with FB primary and CoT secondary, and 10.20 the other way around.  Not a whole lot of difference, so it's not that critical, but at least I can sleep better now, and I will equip my baton in my primary.<br><br>The end result from all this hemming and hawing - to determine the better way to go, check the table.  I don't think there's an easy answer if you are wondering about speed vs damage in your right hand.  The table is out there, fortunately, so the answer is a just a little research away.<br><br>Good Hunting To All!!!<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
